1766
02:07:19,842 --> 02:07:21,385
Never Bugs.

1767
02:07:22,720 --> 02:07:24,346
Little ones.

1768
02:07:46,744 --> 02:07:50,205
That was a great game.

1769
02:07:50,706 --> 02:07:52,708
PETER:
Thank you for believing.

1770
02:07:52,875 --> 02:07:54,877
[♪♪♪]

1771
02:08:28,327 --> 02:08:29,787
I know her.

1772
02:08:30,829 --> 02:08:33,457
She looks like an angel.

1773
02:08:33,624 --> 02:08:37,044
Let's not wake her yet.
Okay.

1774
02:09:23,382 --> 02:09:24,508
Oh.

1775
02:09:24,675 --> 02:09:28,429
My dear child,
have you been up all night?

1776
02:09:29,513 --> 02:09:33,016
I see them in their beds
so often in my dreams.

1777
02:09:33,600 --> 02:09:35,894
When I wake up,
they're still there.

1778
02:09:36,061 --> 02:09:37,396
[GASPS]

1779
02:09:39,523 --> 02:09:41,650
Mom!

1780
02:09:42,276 --> 02:09:43,610
[GASPS]

1781
02:09:48,031 --> 02:09:50,033
[sesame]

1782
02:10:12,431 --> 02:10:14,433
[BELLS JINGLING]

1783
02:10:18,979 --> 02:10:22,441
Tink? Tink? Tink?

1784
02:10:23,233 --> 02:10:24,276
Tink.

1785
02:10:30,032 --> 02:10:31,325
[CHUCKLES]

1786
02:10:31,492 --> 02:10:32,576
Hello.

1787
02:10:35,662 --> 02:10:37,206
Having trouble
with the missus?

1788
02:10:37,372 --> 02:10:39,875
You will have,
by the time you get home.

1789
02:10:45,923 --> 02:10:47,007
Tink.

1790
02:10:48,926 --> 02:10:52,554
Say it, Peter.
Say it and mean it.

1791
02:10:54,014 --> 02:10:55,766
I believe in fairies.

1792
02:10:56,350 --> 02:10:59,228
Do you know that place
between sleep and awake,

1793
02:10:59,728 --> 02:11:01,688
where you still
remember dreaming?

1794
02:11:04,107 --> 02:11:06,318
That's where
I'll always love you,

1795
02:11:07,319 --> 02:11:08,987
Peter Pan.

1796
02:11:11,823 --> 02:11:13,617
That's where I'll be waiting.

1797
02:11:23,293 --> 02:11:25,295
[♪♪♪]

1798
02:11:32,177 --> 02:11:33,512
Ouch.

1799
02:11:33,679 --> 02:11:35,180
Nana!

1800
02:11:35,347 --> 02:11:38,642
Oh, give us a kiss!
Come here, you drool machine!

1801
02:11:38,892 --> 02:11:40,978
Maggie, Moira, Jack!

1802
02:11:43,355 --> 02:11:45,357
[PHONE RINGING]

1803
02:11:46,400 --> 02:11:47,818
Tink?

1804
02:11:49,528 --> 02:11:50,862
[WHISTLING]

1805
02:12:02,916 --> 02:12:04,793
Wow.

1806
02:12:05,669 --> 02:12:09,006
Brad! Hi! Have you been
holding this long?

1807
02:12:09,172 --> 02:12:13,302
Uh-huh. I'm incredible!
Yeah. Never Land.

1808
02:12:13,802 --> 02:12:16,346
Uh-huh. Lost Boys.

1809
02:12:16,513 --> 02:12:19,057
Jim Hook. Duel to the death.
I'll fill you in later.

1810
02:12:19,224 --> 02:12:21,059
Listen, I'd love to chat,

1811
02:12:21,226 --> 02:12:23,478
but I'm gonna climb
a drainpipe now.

1812
02:12:24,104 --> 02:12:26,189
Why?
Because I ran out of fairy dust.

1813
02:12:26,356 --> 02:12:29,109
If not, I would've flown up.
Heh. "Why?"

1814
02:12:33,071 --> 02:12:35,073
[BARKING]

1815
02:12:35,490 --> 02:12:38,577
JACK: There were pirates--!
MAGGIE: And monsters there!

1816
02:12:39,286 --> 02:12:40,329
Just like you said!

1817
02:12:40,495 --> 02:12:42,331
PETER: Maggie, Moira, Jack.
Granny Wendy!

1818
02:12:43,248 --> 02:12:44,374
Let me in.

1819
02:12:45,042 --> 02:12:46,418
Please.

1820
02:12:49,004 --> 02:12:51,423
Excuse me,
do you have an appointment?

1821
02:12:54,009 --> 02:12:57,095
What did I tell you
about this window?

1822
02:12:57,262 --> 02:12:58,764
Always keep it open!

1823
02:12:58,930 --> 02:13:00,015
Ha!

1824
02:13:00,557 --> 02:13:03,518
Never, ever, ever close...

1825
02:13:17,240 --> 02:13:19,242
[PHONE RINGING]

1826
02:13:23,080 --> 02:13:24,623
I have to take this.

1827
02:13:24,790 --> 02:13:29,127
Have you ever known what it's like to
feel the exhilaration of really flying?

1828
02:13:29,294 --> 02:13:31,046
Feel this.

1829
02:13:32,089 --> 02:13:33,590
Where have you been?

1830
02:13:33,757 --> 02:13:35,050
MAGGIE:
Fly me, Daddy. Fly me!

1831
02:13:35,258 --> 02:13:38,762
Anytime, Maggie.
To infinity and back again.

1832
02:13:39,346 --> 02:13:41,056
Hello, Peter.

1833
02:13:41,765 --> 02:13:45,018
I missed the adventure
again, didn't I?

1834
02:13:46,687 --> 02:13:48,772
I think these belong to you.

1835
02:14:01,076 --> 02:14:02,119
Look!

1836
02:14:02,494 --> 02:14:05,747
See, look! I didn't lose
my marbles after all!

1837
02:14:05,914 --> 02:14:07,457
Wendy, look! See?

1838
02:14:07,624 --> 02:14:10,293
I didn't lose my marbles
after all!

1839
02:14:12,087 --> 02:14:14,089
Hello, boy.

1840
02:14:14,923 --> 02:14:16,717
Hello, Wendy lady.

1841
02:14:17,426 --> 02:14:18,635
Give us a skwoodge.

1842
02:14:19,010 --> 02:14:21,012
[♪♪♪]

1843
02:14:29,730 --> 02:14:31,606
Boy, why are you crying?

1844
02:14:32,107 --> 02:14:35,318
I don't know. A tear
for every happy thought.

1845
02:14:35,485 --> 02:14:37,154
One for me?

1846
02:14:37,320 --> 02:14:39,072
One for me?
One for me?

1847
02:14:39,239 --> 02:14:41,491
And one for me!

1848
02:14:41,658 --> 02:14:43,660
[LAUGHING]

1849
02:14:47,831 --> 02:14:49,833
[SCREAMING]

1850
02:14:56,173 --> 02:14:58,175
Seize the day!

1851
02:15:01,595 --> 02:15:04,765
So your adventures are over.

1852
02:15:04,931 --> 02:15:06,433
Oh, no.

1853
02:15:06,600 --> 02:15:08,185
To live...

1854
02:15:08,351 --> 02:15:11,146
To live would be
an awfully big adventure.

1855
02:15:11,938 --> 02:15:13,982
[♪♪♪]

1856
02:15:39,382 --> 02:15:41,384
[♪♪♪]

1857
02:18:44,901 --> 02:18:46,903
[♪♪♪]

